subject: ENGLISH
text: Answer the first question and any two of the others:

subject: ENGLISH
text: Consider to what extent any one of the following Shakespearean characters was morally responsible for the series of events which ended in his death: Richard II, Brutus, Hamlet, King Lear.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Relate the opening scene in any one of Shakespeare's plays and show its importance for the proper understanding of all that follows.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Illustrate some of the ways in which a Shakespearean drama was more suitable for presentation in an Elizabethan than in a modern theater.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Say what is peculiarly characteristic in Milton's or Wordsworth's or Browning's poetic style and choice of subject. If possible, illustrate your reply by quotation from the writer's poems. Or Write a short appreciation of one of the following: Spenser's Epithalamion, Dryden's Alexander's Feast, Burns's The Cotter's Saturday Night, Scott's Marmion, Keats's Ode to a Nightingale, Tennyson's The Lady of Shalott, Mr. Masefield's The Everlasting Mercy.

subject: ENGLISH
text: How do you account for the popularity of satire in the 18th century? Illustrate your answer by reference to some famous examples of this kind of poem.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Describe any one humorous character in a work by any one of the following authors: Addison, Goldsmith, Scott, Dickens, Jane Austen, George Eliot, G.K. Chesterton, P.G. Wodehouse.

subject: ENGLISH
text: Write briefly on any one of the following:

subject: ENGLISH
text: Dr. Johnson as a man of letters;

subject: ENGLISH
text: Carlyle as a historian and writer of English;

subject: ENGLISH
text: Thomas Hardy as a novelist. Or Summarise any piece of literary criticism by either Macaulay or Matthew Arnold of which you strongly approve or disapprove, giving reasons for your view.

subject: ENGLISH
text: What do you regard as the essential features of a good lyric poem? Illustrate, if you can, by quotation. Or Write an appreciation of the historical novel with which you are most familiar.
